SCHOONMAKER-CONNERS CO., Inc., Libelant-Appellee, v. NEW YORK CENT. R. CO., Respondent-Appellant. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 19, 1926.) No. 273. Bigham, Englar & Jones, of New York City (Andrew J. MeElhinney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. William P. Purdy, of New York City, for appellee.

Before HOUGH, MANTON, and HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree (12 F.[2d] 314) affirmed, with costs.
